“import”, with its grammatical variation and cognate expression
means to bring or cause to bring into any component region from
a  place  outside  such  region,  by  land,  sea,  or  air;

(c) all vegetation and other natural products whether or not
requiring  the  periodical  application  of  labour  for  their
production  and  whether  on  or  below  the  surface;

“Minister”  means  the  Minister  charged  with  the  responsibility
for  the  eradication  of  agricultural  pests  and  noxious  plants  and
prevention  of  plant  diseases;

(a)  to the Menteri Besar or Chief Minister, as the case may
be, of the State in Peninsular Malaysia in which the land
specified  in  the  notice  is  situated;

(f) the  control  of,  and  the  conditions  governing  the  import
or export of pests, beneficial organisms, plants and soil
for purposes of controlling and prevention of plant pests;
